[SN]TITLE[SN]
Olympia Horse Show: Carl Hester wins World Cup freestyle title

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Britain's Carl Hester won the freestyle dressage title at the London International Horse Show, with Charlotte Dujardin finishing second.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Media playback is not supported on this device
Olympic, world and European champion Dujardin beat Hester, 48, into second in Tuesday's dressage grand prix.
Hester, who won Olympic team dressage gold with Dujardin, 30, and Laura Tomlinson in 2012, claimed victory on Nip Tuck at Olympia on Wednesday.
Dutchman Hans Peter Minderhoud was third on Glock's Flirt.
Briton Lara Griffith finished fourth on Rubin Al Asad.
Five days of showjumping begins on Thursday, with Britain's world number one Scott Brash in action.
